<emphasis id="AEB47F0703200922FF43B359C95ECB10" box="[142,287,779,800]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<typeStatus id="437B1DB703200922FF43B359C882CB10" box="[142,195,779,800]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="5BC0D89603200922FEE1B359CAACCB10" authority="Meigen, 1824: 56" authorityName="Meigen" authorityPageNumber="56" authorityYear="1824" box="[300,749,778,801]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Porphyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">
<emphasis id="AEB47F0703200922FEE1B359CA62CB10" box="[300,547,779,800]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Porphyrops flavicollis</emphasis>
Meigen, 1824: 56
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="5BC0D89603200922FCEBB096CCFCC8EA" authority="(Meigen, 1824)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[806,1213,196,218]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Achalcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">
<emphasis id="AEB47F0703200922FCEBB096CC45C8E9" box="[806,1028,196,217]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Achalcus flavicollis</emphasis>
(Meigen, 1824)
</taxonomicName>
as designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="F851DEE403200922FCEBB0B1CC4BC8C9" author="Robinson H" box="[806,1034,227,249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 92" refId="ref25093" refString="Robinson H. 1970. Family Dolichopodidae. In: A catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas South of the United States Fasc. 40. Universidade de Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia, 1 - 92." type="book chapter" year="1970">Robinson (1970: 22)</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C7FA31503200922FCEBB143CD03C954" blockId="4.[806,1421,273,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="AEB47F0703200922FCEBB143CB2BC916" box="[806,874,273,294]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Head.</emphasis>
Uppermost postoculars usually darker than lower ones (exc. 
<taxonomicName id="5BC0D89603200922FC35B162CCE4C975" authorityName="Pollet" authorityYear="2005" box="[1016,1189,304,325]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Achalcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costaricensis">
<emphasis id="AEB47F0703200922FC35B162CCE4C975" box="[1016,1189,304,325]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">A. costaricensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5BC0D89603200922FB76B162CD68C974" authorityName="Pollet" authorityYear="2005" box="[1211,1321,303,325]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Achalcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis id="AEB47F0703200922FB76B162CD68C974" box="[1211,1321,303,325]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">A. tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Arista usually longer than first three antennal joints.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C7FA31503200922FCEBB12ECCF8CB11" blockId="4.[806,1422,380,801]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="AEB47F0703200922FCEBB12ECC6AC9A1" box="[806,1067,380,401]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Thorax and abdomen.</emphasis>
Five dc (synapomorphy). No small additional setae between posthumeral, presutural and first two dc bristles. Abdomen with five pubescent segments (synapomorphy). Hypopygium (
<figureCitation id="04FBBF9003200922FCE3B1A5CB32CA3C" box="[814,883,503,525]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[142,220,1826,1845]" captionTargetBox="[158,1407,854,1791]" captionTargetId="figure-331@4.[157,1408,853,1793]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Achalcus flavicollis (Meigen) (male). Hypopygium. AE, aedeagus; CC, cercus; DEP, dorsal process of epandrium; EL, epandrial lobe; ES, epandrial setae; HP, hypandrium; PGO, postgonites; ST, surstylus; VEP, ventral process of epandrium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5431998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5431998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="04FBBF9003200922FC45B1A5CBD6CA3D" box="[904,919,503,525]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[155,233,1833,1852]" captionTargetBox="[194,1395,280,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-55@5.[192,1396,203,1801]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Achalcus flavicollis (Meigen). Hypopygial appendages. A, aedeagus; B, epandrial lobe; C, ventral process of epandrium; D, dorsal process of epandrium; E, surstylus; F, postgonites (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5432000" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5432000/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">2</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium simple, without spines on apex; aedeagus simple, at most with subapical dorsal bend; ventral (not dorsal, as in 
<bibRefCitation id="F851DEE403200922FB64B266CB1FCA59" author="Pollet M &amp; Cumming JM" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" pagination="371 - 385" refId="ref25010" refString="Pollet M, Cumming JM. 1998. Systematic revision of Nearctic species of Achalcus Loew (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) with comments on their phylogeny, ecology and zoogeography. Systematic Entomology 23: 371 - 385." type="journal article" year="1998">Pollet &amp; Cumming, 1998</bibRefCitation>
) epandrial lobe slender with three epandrial setae on shaft (synapomorphy); midventral bristle of surstylus usually without or with only minute apical flag. Legs. Tibia I with one, two or without dorsal bristles. Tibia II with two ad bristles (exc. 
<taxonomicName id="5BC0D89603200922FB3DB29CCD6BCAD3" authorityName="Pollet" authorityYear="2005" box="[1264,1322,718,739]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Achalcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis id="AEB47F0703200922FB3DB29CCD6BCAD3" box="[1264,1322,718,739]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Femur III mostly with strong preapical ad bristle, usually inserted at middle of anterior face.
</paragraph>
<caption id="C8BFF39D03200922FF43B770C949CF5F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5431998" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5431998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5431998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" startId="4.[142,220,1826,1845]" targetBox="[158,1407,854,1791]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="9C7FA31503200922FF43B770C949CF5F" blockId="4.[142,1422,1826,1903]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="AEB47F0703200922FF43B770C8B7CF05" bold="true" box="[142,246,1826,1845]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Figure 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="5BC0D89603200922FECFB770CA6CCF05" authority="(Meigen)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[258,557,1826,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Achalcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">
<emphasis id="AEB47F0703200922FECFB770C98BCF05" box="[258,458,1826,1845]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Achalcus flavicollis</emphasis>
(Meigen)
</taxonomicName>
(male). Hypopygium. AE, aedeagus; CC, cercus; DEP, dorsal process of epandrium; EL, epandrial lobe; ES, epandrial setae; HP, hypandrium; PGO, postgonites; ST, surstylus; VEP, ventral process of epandrium.
</paragraph>
</caption>
